&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own compensation programs across the firm, including base salary, bonus, and incentive structures. Lead annual review cycles, offer decisions, and the rigor of how promotion recommendations are made and documented.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead compensation benchmarking using financial services surveys, including McLagan. Partner with the CHRO on compensation philosophy, job architecture, and the ongoing work of building consistency into how roles are leveled and rewarded across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the design and administration of competitive long-term incentive programs, drawing on experience with complex compensation structures, including deferred compensation arrangements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee benefits programs, including medical, dental, vision, life, and supplemental coverage. Manage vendor relationships, renewals, and open enrollment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own 401(k) plan administration, including compliance, audits, and regulatory filings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage payroll processes with accuracy, appropriate controls, and audit readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure wellness programming is effective and appropriate for our population, including the fitness reimbursement program and Employee Assistance Program, with an eye toward meaningful participation and employee value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead day-to-day HR operations across the employee lifecycle, including onboarding, job changes, leaves, and terminations, with accuracy and a high-quality employee experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a senior advisor on employee relations matters. Partner with the CHRO to resolve complex or sensitive situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Paylocity and Greenhouse (ATS), maintaining data integrity, system configuration, and HR reporting. Identify opportunities to automate and improve how the team works.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and develop a small team of HR professionals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Sets This Role Apart:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A hands-on senior role focused on the operational core of HR: compensation, systems, payroll, benefits, 401(k), employee data, compliance, and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A role for someone who wants to own the HR back office directly, not simply advise from a distance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to strengthen infrastructure, improve processes and controls, close gaps

